-- Air China, Datang International Power Generation: China Equity Preview
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-02T00:24:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/air-china-datang-international-power-generation-china-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in China trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the last close.  The  Shanghai Composite Index , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, gained 75.19, or 2.5 percent, to
3,054.02. The  CSI 300 Index  rose 2.8 percent to 3,473.  Air China Ltd.  (601111 CH): The world’s largest carrier by
market value has received approval from the China Securities
Regulatory Commission to issue no more than 585 million A shares.
The stock gained 2.9 percent to 16.03 yuan.       China Construction Bank Corp.  (601939 CH): The world’s
second-largest lender by market value said it received
regulatory approval for rights offer that will raise 61.7
billion yuan ($9.2 billion), less than the maximum. The shares
gained 2.4 percent to 5.16 yuan.  China Minsheng Banking Corp.  (600016 CH): The lender said
it received approval from China’s banking regulator to upgrade
its representative office in Hong Kong to a branch. The shares
rose 1.1 percent to 5.52 yuan.  Chongqing Brewery Co.  (600132 CH): The brewery said China’s
State-owned Assets Supervision and Administration Commission
approved Carlsberg A/S’s purchase of a 12.25 percent stake in
the Chinese company. The stock added 4.8 percent to 66.09 yuan.  Datang International Power Generation Co.  (601991 CH): The
parent of China’s biggest publicly traded electricity producer
has confirmed plans to inject coal-fired generating plants into
the listed company within five years to eight years and its
Hebei province operations in about five years. Datang gained 1.5
percent to 7.32 yuan.  Jointown Pharmaceutical Group Co.  (600998 CH): The drug
maker said its shares will start trading in Shanghai today after
raising 1.95 billion yuan selling 150 million shares in an
initial public offering last month.  Haitong Securities Co.  (600837 CH): The brokerage said 3.46
billion more shares will become tradable on Nov. 8 after a stock
restructuring. The stock rose 1.5 percent to 12.62 yuan.  Ping An Insurance (Group) Co.  (601318 CH): Shareholders of
China’s second-largest insurer approved the company’s plan to
buy  Shenzhen Development Bank Co.  (000001 CH). Ping An shares
were suspended since Oct. 29. Shenzhen Development gained 0.9
percent to 18.57 yuan.  Tangshan Jidong Cement Co.  (000401 CH): The cement maker
said its parent has bought 7.76 million shares in the listed
company in the last six months in accordance with a plan
announced April 29. The shares gained 3.5 percent to 23.80 yuan.  -- Zhang Shidong , William Bi. Editor:  Glenn J. Kalinoski   To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
